<br>
Keep it the same as the Wizard level 4 spell.<br>
<br>
It is about time at level 64, that an ability my pet got at level 4. The same pet I summon would have taught me how to do that simple thing by now.<br>
<br>
As for over powering us, not really.<br>
<br>
A mage with 2 mobs is a gating mob in PoP. Now with a root, we have a chance to root it, and gate out as your not going to be able to kill 2 mobs.<br>
<br>
As for making it easier to chain a pet, if it hold, it will. On the other hand our soloing days in PoP are over. Unless you use the elemental charm, and with no CC it is dangerous. With a root it helps us.<br>
<br>
Think of it this way. IF an enchanter can charm a higher level mob than a Magician. Can CC better than a Magician. Can root better than a Maggician. Can Stun/Shield Skins/Haste and Slow better than a Magician when using a charmed mob, WHY are so many dead set against us getting a root?<br>
<br>
Is it because we can slow? nope. Is it because we can haste: Nope. Is it because we have pets: YES.<br>
<br>
